Tever Akase, Chief Press Secretary to Governor Samuel Ortom has raised alarm over threat to his life by former Special Adviser to Benue State Governor on Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs, Mr Titus Zam. Akase in a statement made available to DAILY POST said Zam accused him of ‘lying that he approached the governor for appointment. Zam vowed to approach Akase for proof on the street made the allegations in a Facebook post on Thursday. Reacting, Akase called on security agencies to note Zam’s threat against him and hold him responsible should anything happen to him. He said, “My attention has been drawn to a statement made on Facebook by former Special Adviser to Benue State Governor on Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs, Mr Titus Zam, in which he threatened me thus: “Was Terver too honored? What for? For the lies? He told a fat lie that I approached the governor for appointment. I will one day meet this guy on the streets and demand for a proof.” “I do not take the above threat lightly. Titus Zam has to explain before the law, his words of meeting me on the streets. “Meanwhile, I invite security agencies to note Zam’s threat against me. Should anything happen to me or any member of my family, Zam should be held responsible.” See threat below… <img class="aligncenter wp-image-834705 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2aaec0da-9e59-4169-a6d1-5bc944dc95da-746x1024.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="1016" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2aaec0da-9e59-4169-a6d1-5bc944dc95da-746x1024.jpg 746w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2aaec0da-9e59-4169-a6d1-5bc944dc95da-219x300.jpg 219w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2aaec0da-9e59-4169-a6d1-5bc944dc95da.jpg 787w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-834706 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/31dc21c5-7d58-420f-ace3-0144b73a7426-674x1024.jpg" alt="" width="674" height="10